  "text": "Pre-injury health was a self-rated measure (poor, fair, good, very good, excellent). Pain catastrophising was measured at all measurement points by means of the 9-item catastrophising subscale of the Pain-Related Self-Statements Scale (PRSS). This psychometric test has demonstrated reliability and validity [CITATION_1] . Answer categories ranged from 0 to 5 (not at allall the time) [CITATION_2] . Examples of the questions are: 'No matter what I do my pain doesn't change', 'I am a hopeless case'. Higher scores indicate more frequent catastrophising. The sum is calculated and the total score range is 0-45.",
